posts.name: Landon
posts.cooked: Does anyone know where I can find a kit of parts chassis without the gearbox in it because my team is using shifting gearboxes for our robot.

posts.name: EricH
posts.cooked:
You take the kit of parts chassis, and you swap out the gearboxes for shifting ones.

Or you go to https://www.andymark.com/products/am14u5-6-wheel-drop-center-robot-drive-base-first-kit-of-parts-chassis?via=Z2lkOi8vYW5keW1hcmsvV29ya2FyZWE6OkNhdGFsb2c6OkNhdGVnb3J5LzVjZGVjNzRhOTcwOWQ3MWJjZmFiZmZjOQ and dig through the parts list to find the frame parts you need.

posts.name: Peyton Yeung
posts.cooked:
If this is just for CAD purposes, you can delete the Toughbox Assemblies from the AM14U5 model and constrain your own shifting gearboxes.

If you are planning on purchasing an AM14U5 without gearboxes than you can get that at the link below.

AM14U5 with No Gearboxes
